Excuse me. \n< Serena >
Excuse me, shopkeeper. \n< Serena >

more rare, in fact... \n< Boy >
Well, hmm... I'm sorry, but it seems like this book is
not listed in the catalog. \n< Boy >

give us a price for it... \n< Boy >
I see... Well, I didn't have high expectations anyway.
If you can't buy it, that's fine. No big deal. \n< Serena >
You seem a little happy. \n< Boy >
N-no, it's not like that. \n< Serena >
Do you like books? \n< Boy >
Ah, books are wonderful. They nourish the brain. Good
books are like good food. \n< Serena >
Hehe, you're saying something good. My theory is also
that books can be eaten. \n< Boy >
We seem to get along well. I'm Serena, an adventurer. \n< Serena >
Oh, hello there. I am Tim. \n< Tim >
I am an adventurer, for now at least. I'm not good at
violent tasks, so I mostly receive miscellaneous
requests like this... \n< Tim >
I see. Then we might have passed each other
unknowingly at the guild. \n< Serena >
Oh, I don't know about that. I'm not very comfortable
with the atmosphere there... So I try my best to avoid
going there as much as possible... \n< Tim >
Hehe, I agree with that too. The atmosphere there is
not good. First of all, the air is bad. Also, there is
no natural light. \n< Serena >
It feels like the world of adults, doesn't it? \n< Tim >
I am a bad adult... Oh, I just talked about something
pointless. \n< Serena >
I apologize, I'm in a hurry. It was fun, but I can't
stay and talk for too long. \n< Serena >
I see. Your belly is big, so it must be very
difficult... \n< Tim >
Hmm... Well, I suppose so... \n< Serena >
If it's okay with you, please come again. Pregnant
women can't move around much, can they? I think books
or something like that would definitely be useful for
you. \n< Tim >
Oh, I see. That's too bad. \n< Tim >
If it's okay with you, please come again. The
shopkeeper won't be back for a while, but we change
our books every day... \n< Tim >
If you love books, then I think you would enjoy this
shop... I mean, that's just what I think. \n< Tim >
Very well. If I have the time, I will visit again. \n< Serena >
Well then, Lord Tim. Excuse me. \n< Serena >
Ah... I got surprised. \n< Tim >
What a cute girl. Her eyes are as red as rubies. \n< Tim >
Serena, huh... \n< Tim >
I wonder if they will come again... \n< Tim >
Well, it's about time to head back to the brothel. I
wonder what kind of new job it will be... \n< Serena >
